ects of deep time, into the early twentieth century's darkly ironic and uncanny versions. A welcome contribution to the study of the long nineteenth century, this work reveals an unexamined chapter in intellectual history and in the story of the modern self.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAesthetics in literature. 0aSublime, The, in literature. 0aSublime, The. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aLiterature : Literary Theory. 4aLiterature : Nineteenth-Century Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847419940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438474199423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438474199/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles